"TCP Smart offers the most comprehensive voice controlled smart home experience with Alexa. Control your home lighting and other devices hands free. Here is a step by step guide:
(1). Download our ""TCP Smart"" APP in Google Play or iOS App Store;
(2). Launch the app and register a new account (or login if you’ve already registered);
(3). Turn on TCP Smart devices and connect the devices with “TCP Smart” App;
(4). IMPORTANT: You can rename the devices with TCP Smart App. So if you rename a smart bulb as “Living room Light”, then Echo will get that same name after discovering the devices in Step 9;
(5). Download Amazon ""Alexa"" app from Amazon Market, Google Play or iOS App Store, and connect Echo with ""Alexa"" app;
(6). Search the Alexa Skills directory for ""TCP Smart"";
(7). Click “Enable” skill of ""TCP Smart"", then input your account username, password and region on the linking page; make sure the account you enter in this page is the same as the one you login TCP Smart App.
(8). Talk to Echo ""Alexa, discover devices"". Wait till Echo says, "Discover is completed"";
(9). Now all setups are done. Try to talk to Echo to control your devices."
